# TuneVision Support

**Welcome to TuneVision Support.** We are here to help you get the most out of your musical experience.

## Supported Platforms

TuneVision is available on the following Apple platforms:

- **iOS 17+** — iPhone
- **iPadOS 17+** — iPad
- **macOS 14+** — Mac
- **visionOS 1+** — Apple Vision Pro

## Frequently Asked Questions

### Getting Started

**How do I play?**
Tap any instrument button on the screen to produce a note. Each instrument has its own unique layout and sound. Multi-touch is supported, so you can play chords and drum fills with multiple fingers at once.

**Which instruments are free?**
Piano, Xylophone, and Drums are completely free to play with no limits. Six additional instruments (Flute, Guitar, Saxophone, Harp, Pan Flute, and Cat Piano) can be unlocked through in-app purchases.

### Purchases

**How do in-app purchases work?**
Each premium instrument can be unlocked individually for a one-time purchase of $1.99. There is also a bundle option that unlocks all six instruments at a discounted price. All purchases are non-consumable and support Family Sharing, so everyone in your Apple Family can enjoy them.

**Can I try premium instruments before purchasing?**
Yes! Each locked instrument can be played up to 10 times for free so you can explore before you decide to purchase.

**I purchased an instrument but it is still locked.**
1. Make sure your device is signed in to the Apple ID that made the purchase.
2. Close and reopen the app.
3. Open Settings > App Store and make sure "In-App Purchases" is enabled.
4. If the purchase was made on a different family member's device, ensure Family Sharing is active for your Apple Family.
5. Try tapping "Restore Purchases" in the Instrument Store.

If the issue persists, please contact us at the email below.

### Controls

**iPhone & iPad**
- Tap any instrument button to play a note.
- Use multiple fingers for chords or drum fills.

**Mac**
- Click any instrument button to play a note.
- Use multiple mouse clicks or trackpad taps for rapid playing.

**Apple Vision Pro**
- Look at a button and tap to play a note.
- Use the top instrument bar to switch between instruments.

### General

**Does TuneVision collect any data?**
No. TuneVision does not collect personal information, does not display ads, and does not include any third-party tracking. Please see our [Privacy Policy](https://github.com/Meshy-SC/TuneVision-Support/blob/main/PRIVACY_POLICY) for details.

**Does it work offline?**
Yes. All instrument sounds and visuals are included in the app. An internet connection is only needed when making a purchase through the App Store.

**Which devices are supported?**
TuneVision runs on iPhone (iOS 17+), iPad (iPadOS 17+), Mac (macOS 14+), and Apple Vision Pro (visionOS 1+).

### Troubleshooting

**The app is crashing or not responding.**
1. Force-quit the app and reopen it.
2. Ensure your device is running the latest OS version.
3. Update TuneVision to the latest version from the App Store.
4. If the issue persists, please contact us with details about your device and OS version.

